div.p:
                    Mr. Molotov
                     first announced that he wished to state the questions which were up for
                    discussion. They were: 
                        1.

Reparations from Germany and Italy;
                        2.

Economic Principles Regarding Germany;
                        3.

The Report of the Subcommittee on the Council of Foreign
                            Ministers;
                        4.

Trusteeships;


                        5.

The Directive to the Allied Commanders-in-Chief in Germany;
                        6.

Paper on Cooperation in Solving urgent European Economic
                            Problems;
                        7.

Perhaps Iran.
